{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"## Refactor (routing axis) — DONE + green\nReplaced ticket-type scrutiny with container/leaf:\n- `registry.applies()` drops the type-derived `level`; keys on has_children (container/leaf `scope`).\n- `is_mechanical_leaf(plan, *, has_children)` — leaf, not `ticket_type==\"task\"`.\n- `size_factor`/`_ticket_size` drop the `\"epic\"` literal → `has_children`.\n- `PlanContext.level` (type→level map) removed (now unused).\n- `det_floor` P9 file-impact: `not ctx.children` (leaf), dropping the `(\"task\",\"story\",\"bug\")` type set — a childless epic (leaf-shaped) now correctly gets the check.\n- all 32 `criteria_routing.json` applies_at → `scope`: G3/G4=container; code-grounding/impl-detail (E4/A1/G1G2/E6/T5a/T5b/E5/T5d/T6/T9)=leaf; everything else=both. **T5c security is no longer altitude-gated (both)** — the fix.\n- validator rejects legacy `levels`/`container_only` with a migration hint + validates `scope`.\n- E5 rubric prose updated (epic-exclusion → leaf-only). New tests: container/leaf applies, mechanical-leaf, legacy-key rejection, scope validation. 228 plan-review tests pass; `make lint` clean; routing parity gate OK.\n\n## Content fix (Layer 2) — experiments\nHarness = Pass-1 finder over each candidate vs the epic (POS=d251) + local negatives (8a1c, 4702).\n- **Baseline T5c** on d251 (4 samples): never flags the missing Gerrit human/admin auth (flags\n  encryption-at-rest + token-in-logs, or nothing). Negatives: no auth FP. ✓ \"old did not flag\".\n- **C1 (T5c trust-boundary calibration)**: negatives clean (no FP), but POS still misses the auth\n  absence — crowded out by the louder encryption/token findings.\n- **C2 (T10 + endpoint_access_contract bullet)**: T10 is FP-safe (0 findings on local 8a1c — doesn't\n  fire on non-infra), but first-draft bullet also lost the slot to encryption.\n- Root difficulty: the gap is an ABSENCE in a plan dense with OTHER auth (deploy keys, webhook\n  tokens, SSM), read as \"auth handled\"; louder findings win the finder's slots.\n- **C3 (sharp T10 bullet)** under test: forces per-service enumeration of stood-up services + demands\n  HUMAN/ADMIN auth explicitly, and rules that service-to-service creds do NOT satisfy it. T10 home\n  chosen (infra-scoped ⇒ inherently FP-safe on local work; matches the \"endpoint contract\n  completeness\" framing). Deterministic keyword checks rejected for plan PROSE (over-fire; belong to\n  the code-review gate on the *.tf/gerrit.config diff)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782889811202992001,"uuid":"af89dbfc-edec-4100-9bd8-f0ee5b1e63d6"}